In October 2007, Hamilton announced his intention to live in [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Switzerland Switzerland], stating that this was because he wished to get away from the media scrutiny that he experienced living in the UK. Hamilton admitted under questioning on the television show ''[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parkinson_(TV_series) Parkinson]'' that [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taxation_in_the_United_Kingdom taxation] was part of the reason as well.<ref name="BBC">{{cite news|title=Hamilton makes tax move admission|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/beds/bucks/herts/7088652.stm|date=11 November 2007|accessdate=11 November 2007|publisher=BBC News}}</ref> Hamilton received public criticism from UK MPs including Liberal Democrat MP [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bob_Russell_(UK_politician) Bob Russell] for avoiding UK taxes.<ref name="AFP">{{cite news|title=Ecclestone urges more recognition for F1 champ Hamilton|url=http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5jGS3IaJsftaH5JHip7T_TwrcBUMg|date=6 November 2008|accessdate=6 November 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100117064100/http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5jGS3IaJsftaH5JHip7T_TwrcBUMg|archivedate=17 January 2010|df=dmy}}</ref> He settled in [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luins Luins] in [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaud Vaud canton] on [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake_Geneva Lake Geneva];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/Formula_One_drivers_find_peace_in_Switzerland.html?cid=984310|title=Formula One drivers find peace in Switzerland|work=[[Swissinfo]]|publisher=[[SRG SSR idée suisse]]|accessdate=31 August 2010}}</ref> other Formula One drivers, including world champions [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Schumacher Michael Schumacher], [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kimi_R%C3%A4ikk%C3%B6nen Kimi Räikkönen] and [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fernando_Alonso Fernando Alonso], also live in Switzerland.<ref name="BBCNews">{{cite news|title=Hamilton decides to leave Britain|publisher=BBC News|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/motorsport/formula_one/7068001.stm|date=29 October 2007|accessdate=29 October 2007|first=Adam|last=Parsons}}</ref> Hamilton was one of several figures whose tax arrangements were singled out for criticism in a report by the social-justice<ref>"Our Aims" https://www.christianaid.org.uk/about-us/our-aims</ref> charity [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christian_Aid Christian Aid] in 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/tax-evasion-costs-lives-of-56m-children-826252.html|title=Tax evasion 'costs lives of 5.6m children'|work=The Independent|location=London|first=Sean|last=O'grady|date=12 May 2008|accessdate=7 May 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100508051933/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/tax-evasion-costs-lives-of-56m-children-826252.html|archivedate=8 May 2010|df=dmy}}</ref> At the start of 2012, he moved his personal residence from Switzerland to [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monaco Monaco], which is also a tax haven.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2012/may/23/lewis-hamilton-content-monaco|title=Lewis Hamilton feels content in Monaco after getting rid of baggage|first=Paul|last=Weaver|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=23 May 2012|accessdate=23 May 2012|location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Osborne|first=Lucy|title=How 2,000 Britons living in Monaco are costing UK£1bn a year in lost taxes|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2205884/How-2-000-Britons-living-Monaco-costing-UK-1bn-year-lost-taxes.html|accessdate=23 November 2014|newspaper=Daily Mail|location=London|date=20 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-17615784|title=Monaco profile|date=14 May 2014|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=23 November 2014}}</ref> In 2012, Hamilton featured in the [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McLaren McLaren]-produced cartoon ''[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tooned Tooned]'', alongside [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jenson_Button Jenson Button] and comedian [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Armstrong_(comedian) Alexander Armstrong].

In November 2007, Hamilton started dating [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicole_Scherzinger Nicole Scherzinger], the lead singer of the American girl band [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pussycat_Dolls Pussycat Dolls]; it was announced in January 2010 that they split up to focus on their respective careers. However, they were seen together at the [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_Turkish_Grand_Prix 2010 Turkish Grand Prix]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/motorsport/formula_one/8713401.stm|title=Turkish Grand Prix|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 May 2010|accessdate=30 June 2010}}</ref> and at the [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_Canadian_Grand_Prix Canadian Grand Prix] in Montreal, on 13 June 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/motorsport/formulaone/7825194/Canadian-Grand-Prix-Lewis-Hamilton-and-Jenson-Button-secure-McLaren-one-two.html|title=Canadian Grand Prix: Lewis Hamilton and Jenson Button secure McLaren one–two|work=The Daily Telegraph|location=London|date=13 June 2010|last=Cary|first=Tom|accessdate=31 August 2010}}</ref> The couple split up and reunited numerous times between 2011 and 2013,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/formula_one/15481061.stm|title=Lewis Hamilton admits Nicole split makes racing focus 'tough'|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 October 2011|accessdate=27 October 2011|first=Sarah|last=Holt}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/23128225/nicole-scherzinger-and-lewis-hamilton-end-relationship|title=Nicole Scherzinger and Lewis Hamilton end relationship|publisher=BBC Newsbeat|date=1 July 2013|accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref> but appeared to have got back together in November 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/nicole-scherzinger-lewis-hamilton-back-2870468|title=Nicole Scherzinger and Lewis Hamilton back on track after family Thanksgiving|work=The Mirror|date=1 December 2013|accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref> They split up again in February 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11389031/Nicole-Scherzinger-splits-up-with-Lewis-Hamilton-over-marriage-row.html|title=Nicole Scherzinger splits up with Lewis Hamilton over 'marriage row'|date=4 February 2015|work=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=4 February 2015|first=Nicola|last=Harley}}</ref>

